**localStorage - Browser Data Storage Guide**

**üéØ What is localStorage?**
`localStorage` is a web browser API that allows you to store data persistently in the user's browser. Data survives page refreshes, browser restarts, and even system reboots.

**üíæ Basic Storage Operations:**

**Storing Data:**
```javascript
// Store simple string
localStorage.setItem('username', 'Chuks');

// Store number (converted to string)
localStorage.setItem('userAge', '25');

// Store boolean
localStorage.setItem('isLoggedIn', 'true');
```

**Retrieving Data:**
```javascript
// Get string value
const username = localStorage.getItem('username');
console.log(username); // "Chuks"

// Get number (returns string, need conversion)
const age = localStorage.getItem('userAge');
console.log(age); // "25" (string)
console.log(Number(age)); // 25 (number)

// Get boolean
const isLoggedIn = localStorage.getItem('isLoggedIn') === 'true';
console.log(isLoggedIn); // true (boolean)
```

**üì¶ Storing Objects and Arrays:**

**Storing Complex Data:**
```javascript
const user = {
  name: "Chuks",
  age: 21,
  preferences: {
    theme: "dark",
    language: "en"
  }
};

const shoppingCart = ["apple", "banana", "milk"];

// Convert to JSON string before storing
localStorage.setItem('user', JSON.stringify(user));
localStorage.setItem('cart', JSON.stringify(shoppingCart));
```

**Retrieving Complex Data:**
```javascript
// Get and parse objects
const storedUser = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('user'));
console.log(storedUser.name); // "Chuks"
console.log(storedUser.preferences.theme); // "dark"

// Get and parse arrays
const storedCart = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('cart'));
console.log(storedCart[0]); // "apple"
```

**üîç Inspecting localStorage:**

**View All Stored Data:**
```javascript
// Get all keys
